MyBroadband has partnered with digital solutions provider Phakamo Tech to run a cybersecurity survey where two lucky winners will in a Takealot gift voucher valued at R1,000. The survey focuses on businesses’ abilities to protect against security threats proactively, as well as their capabilities in dealing with security issues as they arise. Questions also address topics such as employee cybersecurity training, as well as whether you use any cybersecurity advisory services. The survey comprises a total of eight questions, meaning it can be completed in just a few minutes. If you are a decision maker in your organisation’s IT or cybersecurity departments, you are invited to complete the survey. Visit the competition thread on the MyBroadband forum and follow the instructions to complete the survey and stand a chance to win R2,000.